    <h2>About Jordan Haney</h2>
    <p>Hi! My name is Jordan Haney. I’m 16 years old and currently a junior at Desert Oasis High School. I’ve developed a strong interest in personal finance, especially in teaching others how to manage their money more effectively. One of my favorite methods to talk about is the “money bucket” technique—a simple and smart way to organize finances by dividing income into different categories or goals.</p>
    <p>I believe that learning how to save, budget, and plan financially is something everyone should know, no matter their age. It’s a skill that can change your life, reduce stress, and help you build a better future. That’s why I’m passionate about helping others—especially teens—understand how money works and how to use it wisely.</p>
    <p>In the future, I hope to continue sharing what I know, whether through teaching, workshops, or online content. I want to make finance easy to understand, practical, and even fun for people my age and beyond.</p>
